The paper discusses a problem related to data cleaning, data integration, and information retrieval, which suggests that it could belong to the sub-categories of databases (cs.DB), information retrieval (cs.IR), and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). The use of a bipartite graph and a similarity function to compare elements between sets suggests that it could also belong to the sub-categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC).
